 Port Elizabeth - LabourNet invites you to attend their quarterly seminar outlining HR compliance within South Africa through various industry-related topics. "This quarter we will be providing a holistic look at various compliance aspects and current issues in the workplace, from dealing with load-shedding at work, Social media at the workplace to the latest B-BBEE trends and incident management from a safe work environment viewpoint," LabourNet says. "Don't miss this great opportunity to get up to date with the latest legislative changes requirements and trends, ensuring that your company harnesses the power of HR best practice, and contributes to future growth within the South African economy." Load Shedding – Taking the power back Social Media and the workplace – to twitter or not to twitter Ownership Scorecard B-BBEE Software Incident Management: Efficiencies that technology adds to compliance. Date:       14 June 2019 Time:      09:00 - 13:00 Cost:      R450 p.p EX VAT Venue:    Garden Court Kings Beach Location: La Roche Dr, Humewood, Port Elizabeth, 6013  RSVP:      11 June 2019 Please RSVP to Cresenda Williams on the above RSVP button or alternatively, you can get hold of her on: cwilliams@labournet.com or call 060 977 2173. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 